<h2 id="modify-data-with-good-documentation">modify data with good documentation</h2>

<p>use git</p>

<p>do not modify data by hand, if so, document it thoroughly</p>

<p>save all the parameters and options, you can establish a fixed structure/file to automatically do this</p>

<p>and safe new versions separately from the old ones, in case you accidently erase something important</p>

<h2 id="save-to-disk-frequently">save to disk frequently</h2>

<p>separate by date and dataset</p>

<h2 id="keep-all-portions-executable-separately">keep all portions executable separately</h2>

<p>if they are organized sequentially</p>

<p>write a script to do this rather than comment out each segment every time</p>

<h2 id="make-sure-the-failure-during-execution-does-not-result-in-serious-result">make sure the failure during execution does not result in serious result</h2>

<p>save the state automatically</p>

<p>resume execution from that state</p>

<p>and print out something so that you can visually recognize both</p>

